	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				At lv 19, this spell is still absolutely essential to my survival and it's about the only way I can solo.<BR>
<BR>
Mez, tashan, root, then commence blasting.<BR>
<BR>
Since I've gotten more familiar with the typical duration of this spell, I'm to the point where I can reroot before root would normally wear off and I've had a few battles where the enemy didn't even get to swing at me.<BR>
<BR>
As far as people talking about rooting and running, I have much better luck with mez. Mez wipes the hate list. Soon as it's cast, you can walk away rather than run and zone.<BR>
<BR>
In areas where it's likely for a wandering enemy to join the fight, be sure to take advantage of root to lower your encounter table.<BR>
<BR>
I don't use this spell if I'm grouped with warriors but if I'm with other casters, it's pretty swift when you can just stand back and blast unscathed.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
